HEADWORD: Woe-begone
<hw>Woe"-be*gone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wo
begon</ets>. See <er>Woe</er>, and <er>Begone</er>, <ets>p.
p.</ets>]</ety> <def>Beset or overwhelmed with woe; immersed in grief or
sorrow; woeful.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>woe-begone</qex> was he with pains of love.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

